definition:
A man of the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Sa.9.12; 
 son of: Mephibosheth (H4648); 
 father of: Pithon (H6377), Melech (H4429), Tarea (H8390) and Ahaz (H0271H); also called Mica at 2Sa.9.12; 
Another name of mi.khah (מִיכָה "Micah" H4318H)
 § Micha = "who is like God"
1) son of Mephibosheth
2) a Levite who signed the covenant with Nehemiah
3) father of Mattaniah, a Gershonite Levite and descendant of Asaph
